Spear, lance</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">חֲנִית</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(chanith)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:19\">1SA 13:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:22\">1SA 13:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:7\">1SA 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:7\">1SA 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:45\">1SA 17:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:47\">1SA 17:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:10\">1SA 18:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:11\">1SA 18:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:9\">1SA 19:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam19:10\">1SA 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:33\">1SA 20:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:9\">1SA 21:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:6\">1SA 22:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:8\">1SA 26:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:12\">1SA 26:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:16\">1SA 26:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:22\">1SA 26:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:22\">1SA 26:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:6\">2SA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:23\">2SA 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:23\">2SA 2:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:19\">2SA 21:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:7\">2SA 23:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:18\">2SA 23:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:21\">2SA 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:21\">2SA 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:21\">2SA 23:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:10\">2KI 11:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:11\">1CH 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:20\">1CH 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:23\">1CH 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:23\">1CH 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:23\">1CH 11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:35\">1CH 12:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr20:5\">1CH 20:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr23:9\">2CH 23:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job39:23\">JOB 39:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:18\">JOB 41:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:3\">PSA 35:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:10\">PSA 46:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:5\">PSA 57:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:4\">ISA 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:3\">MIC 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:3\">NAM 3:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab3:11\">HAB 3:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">רֹמַח</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(romach)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:7\">NUM 25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:8\">JDG 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:28\">1KI 18:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:9\">1CH 12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:25\">1CH 12:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr14:7\">2CH 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:5\">2CH 25:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:14\">2CH 26:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:7\">NEH 4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:10\">NEH 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:15\">NEH 4:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer46:4\">JER 46:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek39:9\">EZK 39:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel4:10\">JOL 4:10</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">שֵׁבֶט</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(shevet)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam18:14\">2SA 18:14</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">γαῖσος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(gaisos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt9:7\">JDT 9:7</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">δεξιολάβος</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(dexiolabos)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:23\">ACT 23:23</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">δορά, δόρυ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(dora, doru)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt7:10\">JDT 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt11:2\">JDT 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/EsthGr8:12\">ESG 8:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir29:13\">SIR 29:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc3:15\">3MA 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc5:43\">3MA 5:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3Macc6:5\">3MA 6:5</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κάμαξ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kamax)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc5:3\">2MA 5:3</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">κέντρον</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(kentron)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/4Macc14:19\">4MA 14:19</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">λόγχη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(logchē)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John19:34\">JHN 19:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc5:2\">2MA 5:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc15:11\">2MA 15:11</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">σιβύνη</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(sibunē (zibunē))</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt1:15\">JDT 1:15</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Latin</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">framea</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd13:9\">2ES 13:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Esd13:28\">2ES 13:28</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>The spear was a long, straight rod with a sharp end used for piercing by thrusting. Its circumference was less than the grip of a man’s hand, and its length varied from the height of a man to much longer. It was normally made of wood with a metal head or point (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.5.1 Spearhead&lt;REALIA:2.5.1&gt;</a>). The butt of the spear was also covered with a pointed piece of metal (see <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:23\">2SA 2:23</a>) and was used to stick the spear in the ground or to drive oxen or horses as a goad.</p>\n<p>See the illustration at <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.3.1 Sheath, scabbard&lt;REALIA:2.3.1&gt;</a>.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In battle the spear was held in the middle and thrust at the enemy. Only rarely was it intended for throwing (see <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">2.6 Javelin&lt;REALIA:2.6&gt;</a>).</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>Where possible, translators should choose a word or phrase that indicates that this weapon was held and thrust (much like a knife on the end of a stick) rather than thrown.</p>\n<p>The phrase “lifted up his spear” occurs in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:18\">2SA 23:18</a> and <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:11\">1CH 11:11</a>. <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> gives the correct meaning with “fought with his spear.”</p>\n<p>The meaning of the Greek word <em>dexiolabos</em> in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:23\">ACT 23:23</a> is uncertain. Most translations have “spearmen” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr>, <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr>), “foot soldiers with spears” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr>), “men with spears” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr>), or “light-armed troops” (<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
